The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | 30 killed in 4 Kandahar explosions
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      30 killed in 4 Kandahar explosions
                            
	Kandahar, March 13 (Reuters): Thirty people were killed and dozens hurt after four explosions hit the centre of Afghanistans southern city of Kandahar tonight.        
	According to a Reuters reporter in Kandahar, a shootout between police and militants followed the blasts.        
	Officials said the biggest attack was a suicide raid at the prison in the city where the militants were trying to release prisoners.        
	Reuters reporter Ismail Sameem said the first explosion was near the police chiefs compound and the second near the residence of President Hamid Karzais half-brother Ahmad Wali Karzai who is in Kabul.         
	He said the other blasts took place near the provincial council building, including one about 200 metres from his own home.                                                                                                                                                                  
